<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 08 at 8:57PM CST  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT SOUTHERN SEBASTIAN...EASTERN
PUSHMATAHA...NORTHEASTERN CHOCTAW AND LE FLORE COUNTIES THROUGH 945
PM CST...
At 857 PM CST, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 2 miles southeast of Cameron to 10 miles east of
Nashoba to 3 miles northeast of Kent. Movement was east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Poteau...                         Greenwood...
Heavener...                       Mansfield...
Wister...                         Hackett...
Howe...                           Hartford...
Huntington...                     Midland...
Rattan...                         Cameron...
Octavia...                        Big Cedar...
Excelsior...                      Whitesboro...
Washburn...                       Lake Wister State Park...
Nashoba...                        Burnville...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
